            "answer_text": "The best freelancing websites are not so crowd for beginners. You need to find some marketplaces that match jobs for your profile or where a little competition. Here are some marketplaces that may help you: Writer\u2019s Access - a content writing broker service. Writer\u2019s access also provides prompt and fair mediating services in the event of a dispute or misunderstanding between clients and freelancers.  Periodix - Artificial Intelligence that searches or browses jobs from all over the web for you. It shows projects with the highest chances to be hired for you.  Scripted - is a freelancer community for ghostwriters. All writers on Scripted remain anonymous, and the rights to all content written by freelancers on Scripted are transferred directly to the client.  Believe that you find them useful! P.S. If you like the comment, please Upvote! I appreciate it! ",
